The fire, on South Coast Road, broke out on Friday and engulfed one of the biggest warehouses in the southern hemisphere.It took 400 firemen working 15-hour shifts to put out the main blaze.Smoke from the fire in the 210,000m wax-production factory was fanned by strong winds and blanketed parts of the city. It was visible from 60km away.Nearby residents woke up yesterday to swimming pool surfaces covered with a dark, oily substance.Durban fire chief Enoch Mchunu said it could still be a while before all the flames were put out.Mchunu said 12 fire engines, three water carriers and a number of special vehicles were used.